abstract: Ray Bolger has had a number of peaks in his career his dancing "Slaughter on Tenth Avenue" in "On Your Toes," his floppy limbed Scarecrow in "The Wizard of Oz" and his tour de force of "Where's Charley?" But it is doubtful that he has ever put such a brilliant summation of his talents on display as he is offering in the Empire Room of the Waldorf-Astoria.

abstract: TO his previous superb treatments of the voyages of Magellan and da Gama, Mr. Sanderlin now adds an unequaled abbreviated version of Columbus's voyage taken from the Admiral's own journal and from the biography by his son, Ferdinand. A scrupulously edited blend of the two accounts is the heart of the volume. But to set the Discoverer's achievement in a meaningful frame,..
